  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n              \n              \n              \u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://gizmodo.com/magic-the-gathering-play-booster-pack-2024-set-draft-1850930181\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eMagic: The Gathering\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e has recently been on a \u003cem\u003eFortnite\u003c/em\u003e-esque roll, collaborating with big marquee franchises like \u003ca href=\"https://gizmodo.com/magic-the-gathering-lord-of-the-rings-starter-guide-1850572124\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eThe Lord of the Rings\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://gizmodo.com/nycc-magic-the-gathering-marvel-cards-2000514045\"\u003eMarvel\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"https://gizmodo.com/magic-the-gathering-fallout-spoilers-decks-release-date-1850944802\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eFallout\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. Now, we’ve just got a new look at its upcoming collaboration with Square Enix’s best-selling role playing series, \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp\u003eIn a newly uploaded YouTube video, Square Enix producer Shoichi Ichikawa and Wizards of the Coast product architect Zakeel Gordon released a Nintendo Direct-inspired announcement video teasing the collaboration between the huge franchises. In their sneak peek video, Ichikawa revealed that the partnership will include characters from the first \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy\u003c/em\u003e to the recently released \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy XVI. \u003c/em\u003eYou can check out their video below.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp\u003e\u003ciframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"A Sneak Peek at Magic: The Gathering – FINAL FANTASY\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"about:blank\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen=\"\" data-rocket-lazyload=\"fitvidscompatible\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/a0CgU7bOgNU?feature=oembed\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003cp\u003e“We believe that this combination of the epic storytelling of \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy\u003c/em\u003e and the strategic gameplay of \u003cem\u003eMagic: The Gathering\u003c/em\u003e will be the most exciting entertainment ever on the table,” Ichikawa said.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp\u003e“And for us at Wizards of the Coast, \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy\u003c/em\u003e represents a rich universe that is a natural fit for \u003cem\u003eMagic\u003c/em\u003e‘s gameplay,” Gordon added.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003cp\u003eArguably, the most important tidbit from the \u003cem\u003eMagic: The Gathering\u003c/em\u003e‘s \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy\u003c/em\u003e collab presentation is which characters from its expansive series will get nifty cards. Halfway through the video, Ichikawa revealed that the set would include the following characters: Terra (\u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy VI\u003c/em\u003e), Lightning (\u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy XIII\u003c/em\u003e), Noctis (\u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy XV\u003c/em\u003e), and Cloud (\u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy VII\u003c/em\u003e). Ichikawa also teased iconic monsters like behemoths and chocobos will be a part of the set. Here’s a closer look at even more cards that’ll come with the special collab set.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cdiv id=\"gallery-1\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e \t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://gizmodo.com/magic-the-gathering-just-gave-us-a-tiny-gorgeous-look-at-its-final-fantasy-crossover-2000516861/magic-the-gathering-final-fantasy-emet-selch\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://gizmodo.com/app/uploads/2024/10/magic-the-gathering-final-fantasy-emet-selch.jpg\" alt=\"Magic The Gathering Final Fantasy Emet Selch\" aria-describedby=\"gallery-1-2000516868\" srcset=\"https://gizmodo.com/app/uploads/2024/10/magic-the-gathering-final-fantasy-emet-selch.jpg 1920w, https://gizmodo.com/app